Title: Weight as an Embodiment of Importance: Replications and Extensions
Description: We seek to replicate and extend Jostmann et al.’s (2009) study which showed that the abstract concept of importance is grounded in sensory experiences of weight.
Contributors: Sanja Djordjević, Hans IJzerman
Tags: grounded condition, importance, embodiment, replication

Weight as an Embodiment of Importance: Replications and Extensions
We seek to replicate and extend Jostmann et al.’s (2009) study which showed that the abstract concept of importance is grounded in sensory experiences of weight.
